{
  "texts": [
    "It then aggregates via maximum a posteriori estimation of global neurons.",
    "However, the authors only considered simple MLP architectures.",
    "FedMA [40] extends PFNM to convolutional and recurrent neural networks by matching and averaging hidden elements, specifically channels for CNNs and hidden units for RNNs.",
    "It solves the matched averaging objective by iterative optimization.",
    "Through theoretical analysis, Xiao and Cheng [43] found that global information can be omitted by PFNM."
  ]
